-- Ford Otosan Reports 47% Increase in Second-Quarter Profit on Higher Sales
-- Mark Bentley
-- 2010-07-30T10:49:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-30/ford-otosan-of-turkey-second-quarter-profit-surges-to-125-2-million-liras.html

          
          
             Ford Otomotiv Sanayi AS, the Turkish
unit of Ford Motor Co., said net income in the second
quarter of this year rose 47 percent from a year earlier, driven
by strong sales volumes.  
 Net income increased to 125.2 million liras ($83 million)
in the three months to June from 85 million liras a year
earlier. Ford Otosan was expected to earn 107.8 million liras,
according to the average estimate of four analysts surveyed by
Bloomberg.  
          
          


  


        